text: Hey guys, it’s Ro!

I’m making an update video today because
2014 is coming to an end,

I can’t believe it and there are a bunch
of things going on and I just wanted
to share with you and keep you in the loop.

The 1st update that I have, is that YouTube invited
me to be in YouTube Rewind’s
annual video and it was so much fun filming!

You probably saw some pictures on my social
media, but in case you missed

the video I will put a link down below so
you can go check it out.

It was just really fun, a little recap of
the year. I thought it was, like,
really special!

Then the 2nd update is you guys know that
I read a lot, I’m a little bit of

a book worm, and you guys suggested that I
read Maze Runner and I just finished

that book and I asked you guys on Twitter
what book I should read next, and…

I got a lot of suggestions for Insurgent which
is the 2nd book, right after

Divergent. The movie is coming out, I am hoping
to finish it before the movie
comes out.

But, I’m a little bit of a slow reader,
so we shall see.

But I’ve just started it, and I’m really
excited.

And if you guys are interested in checking
out Audible, it is one

of my ultimate favorite apps, you can go to
Audible.com/RosannaPansino and
you will get a free book. That is Audible.com/RosannaPansino.
3rd update… 3, that’s perfect!

I got a lot of messages saying that we are
almost at 3 million subscribers on YouTube.

And this is more of a thank you than an update.
I just wanted to thank you all

for being so supportive and wanted to thank
you for subscribing.
You guys are amazing and I love making videos.

So this, this update is just a thank you, thank
you, thank you, thank you!
YAY! Go Nerdy Nummies!

The 4th update is I just recently recorded
some YouTubers react with

The Fine Brothers and I’m not sure when
those are coming out but as soon as they

do I will post them on all my social media
and I’ll link to it in this video

down below so you can go check ‘em out.
I love filming with those guys, they

always surprise me with whatever they’re
showing so I hope you guys get a
kick out of it.

5th update is, I was on my very first magazine
cover!

I got to share the experience with 2 awesome
ladies, Michelle Phan and
Bethany Mota, I’ll put a picture over here.

It was just one of those crazy things, so
surreal and unexpected and I just

wanted to share that with you guys. It was
really exciting.

Also, I got a lot of questions from you guys
about what dress I was wearing

on the cover of the magazine and I found that
dress at H&M when I was shopping

with my sister. Nothing too fancy, keeping
it simple…
Lastly I am working on a 2014 recap video.

I just thought it would be really special
to take all of the projects and events

and everything that we did this year and put
it into a video, for da memories!

And, I am so excited for 2015, I got a lot
of projects in the works and I can’t
wait to share them with you.

I hope you guys are having good holidays,
I’ll talk to you later.
Bye-bye!

If you guys want to check out any more vlogs,
you can click here or here…
Up ‘dere.
Ro-dolph the red nose reindeer,
Hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm,
hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm-hmmm.

This would actually be gigantic, this is a
huge nose!
